Twitter plans to start testing several new features, including a subscription-based program. The program dubbed "super follows" will allow users earn revenue from followers by offering exclusive content. A spokesperson for Twitter said the company had been examining and rethinking the incentives of their service. "— the behaviors that our product features encourage and discourage as people participate in conversation on Twitter," "Exploring audience funding opportunities like Super Follows will allow creators and publishers to be directly supported by their audience and will incentivize them to continue creating content that their audience loves," the spokesperson said as quoted by NBC According to Forbes, during its annual Analyst Day presentation Thursday, the company showed a mock screenshot of a Super Follow account charging $4.99 per month(Sh547). The exclusive content could consist of "bonus tweets, access to a community group, subscription to a newsletter, or a badge indicating your support."